This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for generating adversarial examples using feed-forward neural networks. It also involves training these networks in a self-supervised manner. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the effectiveness of the proposed method is analyzed on MNIST classifiers and the ImageNet classifier Inception ResNet v2. 

Additionally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a topic of interest in the AI community. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as adversarial attacks on deep neural networks are a security concern. 

Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed method involves training feed-forward neural networks to generate adversarial examples.
